
Topics:

  Drop-Box ---> select form element

  Overflow:
    handling overflow in an element/tag
    visible ---> default value which make the overflow visible
    hidden --> hides the overflowing content
    scroll --> provides a scroll bar irrespective of overflow content
    auto --> provides a scroll bar only when there is a overflowing content

    shorthand:
      overflow: auto scroll; ---> overflow-x: auto; overflow-y: scroll;

  Measurements/Units:
    Units used in CSS

    Absolute Unit: 
      px - pixel, pt - point, pc - picas
      1px = 1/96th of an inch

      1pt = point 1/72th of an inch

      1pc = picas 12 * 1pt or 1/6th of inch

    Relative Units:
      %, vh, vw
      % --> percent
        1% -> one percent of the parent 
      vh --> viewport height
        1vh -> 1% of the view port height
      vw --> viewport wiodth
        1vw -> 1% of the view port width

      empherical Units:
      em, rem ---> root em
        1rem = fontsize of the root element ( Initial Containing Block )
        1em = fontsize of the parent element

        2rem = 2 * fontsize of the root element ( Initial Containing Block )
        2em = 2 * fontsize of the parent element

  fonts: google fonts https://fonts.google.com/
    Step1: Select a desired font family and add it to view list
    Step2: copy link tag  wit rel styleheet
    Step3: Paste it in the body
    Step4: use the font-family in font-family prop

